name: Renn Shaver
text: Well I have this location a chance despite the reviews, and I wish I hadn't. The kids running the front register was nice and courteous. No issues picking up my order. However, the food itself was beyond bland. You're seriously better off â€¦More

text: These reviews are funny. The pizza taste like every other Pizza Hut I have been to. Never had a problem here. I love the "Can't make my pizza because of the printer" statement. Bravo to you lady. Obviously your order never printed out, or â€¦More

text: Quite place that can bust out a pizza with 15 minutes or less. Simple booths and a few arcade games around to pass the time.

text: This is probably the poorest run Pizza Hut in Orange County. Phoned in an order on the way home from work. Got there and had to wait probably 10 minutes for service (not the first time either). Ordered a large pan pizza. Was sliced into 8 â€¦More

text: Worst Pizza Hut ever. Ordered a pizza online and it took over two hours for delivery. And it was cold. And the only excuse the manager could make was that their printer broke!!!!!!! So u couldn't make pizza bc your printer broke?

text: Well, I have no complaints,  too bad if other people had them,  chicken wings are the best,  lol @ the printer issue !!!!

text: The people complain a lot about this place but my experiences with them have been always good, good service and good pizza, I guess the actitud of the people is not the best.

name: jesse Murphy
text: Don't offer the national promotions. Your pizza isn't good enough to hold out on promotions. Go to San Giavoni in Rancho Santa Margarita $9.99 cheese pizza. That actuall has real cheese on it!!
